<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>救生艇新闻：博客——保护人类</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Sun, 08 Mar 2026 01:08:58 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>安德鲁·杨：全民基本收入（UBI）之前的全民健康保险（UHI）</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/andrew-yang-ubi-before-uhi</link><description>&lt;img src="https://politepol.com/fd/NjxHZtldG2if.xml" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Sun, 08 Mar 2026 01:08:55 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/andrew-yang-ubi-before-uhi</guid></item><item><title>机器人手术切除了 79 岁老人难以触及的尾状叶肿瘤</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/robotic-surgery-removes-hard-to-reach-caudate-lobe-tumor-in-a-79-year-old</link><description>由于其独特的解剖位置和复杂的血管关系，尾状叶（肝脏的深部、难以到达的部分）肿瘤切除被认为是肝外科中技术上最具挑战性的手术之一。波士顿大学 Chobanian &amp;amp; Avedisian 医学院的研究人员现在表明，即使是老年患者，也可以使用手术机器人安全地切除尾状叶，并且仍然可以完全切除癌症。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/robotic-surgery-removes-hard-to-reach-caudate-lobe-tumor-in-a-79-year-old.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Sun, 08 Mar 2026 00:53:55 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/robotic-surgery-removes-hard-to-reach-caudate-lobe-tumor-in-a-79-year-old</guid></item><item><title>手写与打字：30 项大脑研究揭示哪种方式对您的大脑更好</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/handwriting-vs-typing-30-brain-studies-reveal-which-is-better-for-your-brain</link><description>来自文章： &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/handwriting-vs-typing-30-brain-studies-reveal-which-is-better-for-your-brain.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Sun, 08 Mar 2026 00:38:55 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/handwriting-vs-typing-30-brain-studies-reveal-which-is-better-for-your-brain</guid></item><item><title>模拟假设得到科学支持</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/the-simulation-hypothesis-gets-scientific-backing</link><description>&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/the-simulation-hypothesis-gets-scientific-backing.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Sun, 08 Mar 2026 00:23:55 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/the-simulation-hypothesis-gets-scientific-backing</guid></item><item><title>Senovax 采取了一种新颖的方法</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/senovax-takes-a-novel-approach</link><description>&lt;img src="https://politepol.com/fd/NjxHZtldG2if.xml" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Sun, 08 Mar 2026 00:08:55 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/senovax-takes-a-novel-approach</guid></item><item><title>一种提供抗体的新方法可以使患者的治疗变得更加容易</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/a-new-way-to-deliver-antibodies-could-make-treatment-much-easier-for-patients</link><description>由于每次剂量需要大量抗体，因此癌症和其他疾病的抗体治疗通常通过静脉注射。这意味着患者每次治疗都必须去医院，他们可能要花几个小时接受输液。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/a-new-way-to-deliver-antibodies-could-make-treatment-much-easier-for-patients.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Sat, 07 Mar 2026 23:53:55 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/a-new-way-to-deliver-antibodies-could-make-treatment-much-easier-for-patients</guid></item><item><title>我们所知道的关于宇宙的一切——以及一些我们不知道的事情</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/everything-we-know-about-the-universe-and-a-few-things-we-dont</link><description>宇宙有多大？它是什么形状？它的扩张速度有多快？什么时候结束？我们在宇宙学知识现状的基本指南中回答了这些问题以及更多问题&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/everything-we-know-about-the-universe-and-a-few-things-we-dont2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Sat, 07 Mar 2026 23:38:55 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/everything-we-know-about-the-universe-and-a-few-things-we-dont</guid></item><item><title>“长寿分子标签”免疫细胞图谱：识别主要免疫细胞亚群及其潜在分子调控机制</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/the-immune-cell-atlas-of-longevity-molecular-tag-identification-of-principal-immune-cell-subsets-and-their-underlying-molecular-regulatory-mechanisms</link><description>免疫衰老是衰老过程的一个关键方面。百岁老人作为“健康老龄化”的自然模型，表现出独特的免疫“补偿适应”机制，有助于维持免疫稳态。然而，所涉及的特定免疫细胞亚群以及这些表型特征背后的分子机制仍不完全清楚。在这项研究中，我们将东亚人群整个生命周期的单细胞 RNA 测序数据与广西百岁老人群体的大量转录组数据进行了整合。利用 Scissor 算法，我们积极识别了免疫细胞亚群 (Scissor &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/the-immune-cell-atlas-of-longevity-molecular-tag-identification-of-principal-immune-cell-subsets-and-their-underlying-molecular-regulatory-mechanisms2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Sat, 07 Mar 2026 23:23:55 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/the-immune-cell-atlas-of-longevity-molecular-tag-identification-of-principal-immune-cell-subsets-and-their-underlying-molecular-regulatory-mechanisms</guid></item><item><title>Strehler-Mildvan 死亡率相关性源于老龄化变异性的变化</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/the-strehler-mildvan-mortality-correlation-arises-from-changes-in-the-variability-of-ageing</link><description>随着全球人类预期寿命持续延长，通过延长健康寿命来防止发病率扩大变得越来越重要。人口寿命可以通过不同的方式延长，例如通过生存曲线的矩形化（陡峭化）或三角形化（平坦化）。这两种人口统计变化，特别是矩形化，在人类和模式生物群体中经常发生，但它们的生物决定因素以及对健康寿命和发病率的影响在很大程度上是未知的。值得注意的是，当 Gompertz 死亡率模型（捕捉死亡率指数年龄增长）的参数反向变化时，这些寿命延长模式就会发生，这是一种被广泛报道的现象，称为斯特雷勒-米尔德万相关性，其生物学基础也仍然无法解释。因此，我们调查了 30 名患者的纵向健康状况、发病率和寿命。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/the-strehler-mildvan-mortality-correlation-arises-from-changes-in-the-variability-of-ageing.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Sat, 07 Mar 2026 23:08:55 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/the-strehler-mildvan-mortality-correlation-arises-from-changes-in-the-variability-of-ageing</guid></item><item><title>葡萄糖代谢减少和伴侣减少是衰老成纤维细胞生存所需的独特特征，丙酮酸脱氢酶是有效的衰老目标</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/decreased-glucose-metabolism-and-declined-chaperones-are-unique-features-required-for-the-survival-of-senescent-fibroblasts-and-pyruvate-dehydrogenase-is-a-potent-senolytic-target</link><description>通过对电离辐射诱导的人类衰老 BJ 成纤维细胞的整体蛋白质组学分析，鉴定出 178 种丰度变化至少 4 倍或更大的细胞蛋白，代表了衰老成纤维细胞的细胞景观。功能富集和生物学实验表明，葡萄糖代谢降低、ATP 和 α-KG 产生减少以及伴侣蛋白减少是与衰老成纤维细胞相关的最显着特征。此外，这些蛋白质组特征与其经 RT-PCR 证实的转录改变密切相关。分别抑制丙酮酸脱氢酶（向TCA循环提供乙酰辅酶A的关键酶）或谷氨酰胺酶GLS1（补充TCA循环中间体α-KG的关键酶）或抑制Hsp90（分子伴侣的重要成员）导致选择性杀死衰老成纤维细胞，表明TCA循环或分子伴侣在细胞衰老的存活和维持中的重要作用。最重要的是，共同抑制 TCA 循环和 Hsp90 可以增强对衰老成纤维细胞以及治疗诱导的衰老癌细胞的选择性杀伤，并减轻老年小鼠的身体功能障碍，这表明 TCA 循环和伴侣对细胞衰老的协同调节。因此，我们的分析揭示了衰老正常细胞存活和维持的关键细胞特征，证明丙酮酸脱氢酶是选择性消除衰老的新型且有效的衰老靶点。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/decreased-glucose-metabolism-and-declined-chaperones-are-unique-features-required-for-the-survival-of-senescent-fibroblasts-and-pyruvate-dehydrogenase-is-a-potent-senolytic-target2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Sat, 07 Mar 2026 22:53:55 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/decreased-glucose-metabolism-and-declined-chaperones-are-unique-features-required-for-the-survival-of-senescent-fibroblasts-and-pyruvate-dehydrogenase-is-a-potent-senolytic-target</guid></item></channel></rss>